oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Margaret Croft and her friend reading
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of Margaret Croft and an unidentified woman from the Crofts' Cuba scrapbook. Written next to the photo in the scrapbook is "26 F St." The women are sitting in chairs against a wooden fence looking at a book. Reverse: "Taken on April 30, 1905. Havana, Cuba."
This is the first of two houses the Crofts owned in Havana, located at 26 F Street in Vedado. The second house was located at the corner of 19 and F Streets, Vedado.
